## Row {height="72%"}

```{r}
#| title: Subscription Outcome Distribution
bank |>
  count(subscribed) |>
  mutate(percent = n / sum(n)) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = subscribed, y = percent, fill = subscribed)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_text(aes(label = percent(percent, accuracy = 0.1)), vjust = -0.4) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format(), limits = c(0, 1)) +
  labs(
    x = NULL,
    y = "Share of Contacts",
    title = "Most contacted customers did not subscribe",
    subtitle = "This shows the overall challenge of converting bank marketing contacts into subscriptions."
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
```

